For a more complete understanding of the present invention and the advantages thereof, reference is now made to the following description taken in conjunction with the accompanying drawings in which:


FIG. 1 is a block diagram of a hyperspectral long wave infrared (LWIR) sensor system in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 2 is a flow diagram illustrating data collection, processing and transfer;


FIG. 3 is a schematic layout description for a hyperspectral infrared detector in accordance with the present invention having four pitch dimension regions with each pitch region having four width dimensions;


FIG. 4 is a representation of the infrared responsivity of a hyperspectral detector in accordance with the present invention having sixteen detector bands tuned individually across the 8-12 micron infrared band.


FIG. 5 is a plan view of a portion of a hyperspectral infrared detector corresponding to the configuration shown in FIG. 3;


FIG. 6 is a perspective, cutaway view of a portion of a hyperspectral infrared detector focal plane array in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 7 is a schematic illustration of an alternative configuration for a hyperspectral infrared detector in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 8 is a schematic illustration of an alternative configuration for a hyperspectral infrared detector in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 9 is a schematic illustration of an alternative configuration for a hyperspectral infrared detector in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 10 is a further configuration of a hyperspectral detector in accordance with the present invention, but which includes a central portion with an anti-reflective coating; and
